t: Lord,*sp who shall abide in thy tabernacle? who shall dwell in thy holy hill?
He*p that walketh uprightly, and worketh righteousness, and speaketh the truth in his heart.
He*p that backbiteth not with his tongue, nor doeth evil to his neighbour, nor taketh up a reproach against his neighbour.
In*p whose eyes a vile person is contemned; but he honoureth them that fear the Lord.*s He that sweareth to his own hurt, and changeth not.
He*p that putteth not out his money to usury, nor taketh reward against the innocent. He that doeth these things shall never be moved.
